I'll provide you with a detailed style guide based on the actual Zenith Notes website ([https://zenith-notes.vercel.app/](https://zenith-notes.vercel.app/)). This guide will include color codes, margins, and other design values to help you build the support page on your own. I'll ensure the design is responsive for mobile devices as well.

Here's a comprehensive style guide for your Zenith Notes support page, based on the actual website:

1. Color Palette:

1. Primary Blue: #2563eb
2. Background Color: #f8fafc
3. Text Color (Dark): #0f172a
4. Text Color (Light): #64748b
5. White: #ffffff
6. Border Color: #e2e8f0
7. Button Hover: #1d4ed8



2. Typography:

1. Font Family: Inter, sans-serif
2. Base Font Size: 16px (1rem)
3. Line Height: 1.5



3. Layout:

1. Max Width for content: 1280px
2. Padding for main content: 1rem (16px) on mobile, 1.5rem (24px) on desktop



4. Header:

1. Height: 4rem (64px)
2. Logo Font Size: 1.5rem (24px)
3. Logo Font Weight: 700 (bold)
4. Navigation Item Spacing: 1.5rem (24px) between items
5. Navigation Font Size: 0.875rem (14px)
6. Navigation Font Weight: 500 (medium)



5. Main Content:

1. H1 Font Size: 2.25rem (36px) on desktop, 1.875rem (30px) on mobile
2. H1 Font Weight: 700 (bold)
3. H1 Margin Bottom: 2rem (32px)
4. Section Spacing: 3rem (48px) between major sections



6. Card Design:

1. Background Color: #ffffff
2. Border Radius: 0.5rem (8px)
3. Box Shadow: 0 1px 3px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1), 0 1px 2px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06)
4. Padding: 1.5rem (24px)



7. FAQ Section:

1. Question Font Size: 1.125rem (18px)
2. Question Font Weight: 600 (semibold)
3. Answer Font Size: 1rem (16px)
4. Spacing between Q&A pairs: 1.5rem (24px)



8. Contact Form:

1. Label Font Size: 0.875rem (14px)
2. Label Font Weight: 500 (medium)
3. Input/Textarea Padding: 0.5rem (8px) vertical, 0.75rem (12px) horizontal
4. Input/Textarea Border: 1px solid #e2e8f0
5. Input/Textarea Border Radius: 0.375rem (6px)
6. Button Padding: 0.5rem (8px) vertical, 1rem (16px) horizontal
7. Button Font Size: 0.875rem (14px)
8. Button Font Weight: 500 (medium)
9. Button Border Radius: 0.375rem (6px)



9. Other Contact Info:

1. Icon Size: 1.5rem (24px) x 1.5rem (24px)
2. Icon Color: #2563eb
3. Text Font Size: 1rem (16px)
4. Spacing between contact methods: 2rem (32px)



10. Footer:

1. Background Color: #f1f5f9
2. Text Color: #64748b
3. Padding: 1.5rem (24px) vertical
4. Font Size: 0.875rem (14px)



11. Responsive Breakpoints:

1. Mobile: Up to 639px
2. Tablet: 640px to 1023px
3. Desktop: 1024px and above



12. Responsive Adjustments:

1. On mobile:

1. Single column layout for all sections
2. Reduce horizontal padding to 1rem (16px)
3. Reduce font sizes by about 10-15%



2. On tablet:

1. Two-column layout for FAQ and Contact sections
2. Increase horizontal padding to 1.5rem (24px)



3. On desktop:

1. Maintain two-column layout
2. Max-width container for content






13. Accessibility:

1. Button and Link Hover States: Darken background color slightly (#1d4ed8)
2. Focus States: Add a visible outline (2px solid #2563eb) with a 2px offset



14. Transitions:

1. For hover effects: 0.2s ease-in-out





When implementing your support page, start with a mobile-first approach and then use media queries to adjust the layout and sizes for larger screens. This will ensure your design is responsive and works well on both mobile and desktop devices.

Remember to implement proper semantic HTML structure and use appropriate ARIA attributes where necessary to ensure accessibility.

As you build this page, focus on recreating the visual design and layout. Don't worry about implementing complex functionality like form submissions or interactive FAQ toggles at this stage. You can add those features as you progress in your studies.

Feel free to ask if you need any clarification on these design specifications or if you want advice on implementing any specific part of the design!